byline.contributor: Jonathan Martin contributed reporting. Kitty Bennett contributed research.

abstract: Former Florida governor Jeb Bush has yet to declare his candidacy in 2016 presidential race, but he is far outpacing potential Republican rivals in fundraising.
lead_paragraph: Even as the former Florida governor positions himself as a Washington outsider, he seems to have mastered the skill of tapping into the money-raising clout of the city’s lobbyists, political operatives, lawyers and business leaders.

headline.main: Jeb Bush Returns to the Washington Fund-Raising Well
headline.print_headline: Bush Uses Well-Honed Skills in Tapping Washington’s Fund-Raising Well
